List all nodes of a given type which are present in your environment.

Usage:
  kwm nodes [all etcd controlplane worker]

Examples:
  # Quick hack illustrating how this command finds nodes.
  KWM_ROLE_one=etcd KWM_ROLE_two="controlplane worker" kwm nodes all
  KWM_ROLE_one=etcd KWM_ROLE_two="controlplane worker" kwm nodes etcd
  KWM_ROLE_one=etcd KWM_ROLE_two="controlplane worker" kwm nodes worker
  KWM_ROLE_one=etcd KWM_ROLE_two="controlplane worker" kwm nodes controlplane

  # Display etcd install script for every etcd node.
  kwm nodes etcd | xargs -n 1 kwm render etcd-node

  # Execute etcd install script for every etcd node.
  kwm nodes etcd | xargs -n 1 -P 5 kwm render etcd-node | bash
